## Aider-specific

- **Edit modes**: prefer `code` for narrow edits, `architect` when the task spans
  multiple files (the architect plans, the editor model writes diffs).
- **Don't `/run` arbitrary scripts** unless I explicitly ask. Suggest the command
  instead so I can review.
- **`/add`/`/drop` discipline**: keep the context tight. If a file isn't being
  edited, drop it. Large irrelevant context degrades local-model output more than
  cloud models — keep local sessions especially lean.
- **No surprise commits**: `auto-commits` is off in config. Don't enable per-session.
- **Whole-file edit format**: when working with the local Qwen model, edits resend
  the whole file. Keep functions reasonable size; split monoliths before editing.
